                  <m:msub>
                    <m:mi>s</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>N</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msub>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mn>2N</m:mn>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                    </m:mfrac>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{s rSub { size 8{N} }  \( t \) = {  {2N+1}  over  {T} } } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id13768440">The first zero of sN(t) is at</para>
    <para id="id13768468">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>2N</m:mn>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mfrac>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{t= {  {T}  over  {2N+1} } } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id13768531">Thus, as N → ∞, each lobe gets larger and narrower. To determine if each lobe acts as an impulse, we need to find its area.</para>
    <para id="id13768553">The area of each period of sN(t) is simply</para>
    <para id="id13768581">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mtext>Area</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:msubsup>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">∫</m:mo>
                        <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mrow>
                                <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                                <m:mi>T</m:mi>
