      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id14492841">Therefore, the Fourier transform of a periodic impulse train in time is a periodic impulse train in frequency.</para>
    <figure id="id14492850">
      <media id="id8732172" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics6-e2a5.png" mime-type="image/png" height="122" width="342"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id14492874">3/ Relation of Fourier series spectrum to Fourier transform of a periodic impulse train</para>
    <figure id="id14492886">
      <media id="id1164821167736" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics7-5204.png" mime-type="image/png" height="134" width="476"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id14492910">Therefore, the Fourier transform of the periodic impulse train has an impulse at the frequency of each Fourier series component and the area of the impulse equals the Fourier series coefficient.</para>
    <para id="id14492917">III. FOURIER TRANSFORM OF AN ARBITRARY PERIODIC FUNCTION</para>
